str:Concept.com:Name: Accumulated changes in fair value due to credit risk
str:Concept.com:Description: Accumulated changes in fair value due to credit risk in accordance with Part 2.46 of Annex V to Implementing Regulation (EU) No 680/2014.

str:Concept.com:Name: Accumulated impairment
str:Concept.com:Description: The amount of loss allowances that are held against or are allocated to the instrument on the reporting reference date. This data attribute applies to instruments subject to impairment under the applied accounting standard. Under IFRS, the accumulated impairment relates to the following amounts: (i) loss allowance at an amount equal to 12-month expected credit losses; (ii) loss allowance at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses. Under GAAP, the accumulated impairment relates to the following amounts: (i) loss allowance at an amount equal to general allowances; (ii) loss allowance at an amount equal to specific allowances.

str:Concept.com:Name: Accumulated write-offs
str:Concept.com:Description: Cumulative amount of principal and past due interest of any debt instrument that the institution is no longer recognising because they are considered uncollectible, independently of the portfolio in which they were included. Write-offs could be caused both by reductions in the carrying amount of financial assets recognised directly in profit or loss and by reductions in the amounts of the allowance accounts for credit losses set off against the carrying amount of financial assets.

str:Concept.com:Name: Accounting classification
str:Concept.com:Description: Accounting portfolio where the instrument is recorded in accordance with the accounting standard – IFRS or national GAAP –under Regulation (EU) 2015/534 (ECB/2015/13) applied by the observed agent's legal entity.

str:Concept.com:Name: Accounting framework for solo reporting
str:Concept.com:Description: Information on the accounting framework used by the entity when reporting on a solo basis. The information provided by NCAs is used to calculate the Accounting standard attribute to EBA (ACC_STD).

str:Concept.com:Name: Accrued interest (accounting)
str:Concept.com:Description: The amount of accrued interest on loans at the reporting reference date as defined in Regulation (EU) No 1071/2013 (ECB/2013/33). In accordance with the general principle of accruals accounting, interest receivable on instruments should be subject to on-balance sheet recording as it accrues (i.e. on an accruals basis) rather than when it is actually received (i.e. on a cash basis).

str:Concept.com:Name: Annual turnover
str:Concept.com:Description: Annual sales volume net of all discounts and sales taxes in accordance with Recommendation 2003/361/EC. Equivalent to the concept of 'total annual sales' in Article 153(4) of Regulation (EU) No 575/2013.

str:Concept.com:Name: Interest rate
str:Concept.com:Description: Annualised agreed rate or narrowly defined interest rate in accordance with Regulation (EU) No 1072/2013 of the European Central Bank (ECB/2013/34).

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of default status
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the default status is considered to have arisen.

str:Concept.com:Name: End date of the interest-only period
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the interest-only period ends. Interest-only is an instrument for which, for a contractually set period, only the interest on the principal balance is paid, with the principal balance remaining unchanged.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of enterprise size
str:Concept.com:Description: The date to which the value provided in the ‘enterprise size’ refers. This is the date of the latest data used to classify or review the classification of the enterprise.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of forbearance and renegotiation status
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which a forbearance or renegotiation status as reported under 'status of forbearance and renegotiation' is considered to have occurred.

str:Concept.com:Name: Inception date
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the current contractual relationship originated, i.e. the date on which the contract agreement became binding for all parties.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of initiation of legal proceedings
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the legal proceedings, as reported under the attribute ‘status of legal proceedings’, were initiated. This date should be the most recent relevant date prior to the reporting date and should only be reported if the data attribute 'Status of legal proceedings' has a value other than 'No legal actions taken'.

str:Concept.com:Name: Legal final maturity date
str:Concept.com:Description: The contractual maturity date of the instrument, taking into account any agreements amending initial contracts.

str:Concept.com:Name: Maturity date of the protection
str:Concept.com:Description: The contractual maturity date of the protection, which is the earliest date at which the protection may terminate or be terminated, taking into account any agreements amending initial contracts.

str:Concept.com:Name: Next interest rate reset date
str:Concept.com:Description: The date that the next interest rate reset, as defined in Part 3 of Annex I to Regulation (EU) No 1071/2013 (ECB/2013/33), takes place. If the instrument is not subject to a future interest rate reset, its legal final maturity date will be reported.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of original protection value
str:Concept.com:Description: The date of the protection’s original value, i.e. the date on which the latest appraisal or valuation of the protection was carried out prior to its initial receipt as a credit protection.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of the performing status of the instrument
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the performing status is considered to have been established or changed.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of protection value
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the latest appraisal or valuation of the protection was carried out prior to the reporting reference date.

str:Concept.com:Name: Date of past due
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the instrument became past due in accordance with Part 2.48 of Annex V to Implementing Regulation (EU) No 680/2014. This is the latest such date prior to the reporting reference date and it is to be reported if the instrument is past due on the reporting reference date.

str:Concept.com:Name: Reference date
str:Concept.com:Description: Reporting agents shall report credit data as recorded on the following reporting reference dates: (a) for monthly transmissions, on the last day of each month; (b) for quarterly transmissions, on the last day of March, June, September and December.

str:Concept.com:Name: Settlement date
str:Concept.com:Description: The date on which the conditions specified in the contract are or can be executed for the first time, i.e. the date on which financial instruments are initially exchanged or created.

str:Concept.com:Name: Número de Registro Unico de Contribuyentes (RUC)
str:Concept.com:Description: Tax Identification Number

str:Concept.com:Name: Economic activity
str:Concept.com:Description: Classification of counterparties according to their economic activities, in accordance with the NACE revision 2 statistical classification as laid down in Regulation (EC) No 1893/2006 of the European Parliament and of the Council.

str:Concept.com:Name: Aruandja kood (fondi kood)
str:Concept.com:Description: Unique identifier for investment and pension funds issued by the central bank and used in the reporting.

str:Concept.com:Name: Äriregistri kood (rg-kood)
str:Concept.com:Description: Commercial registry code for state and local government agencies, NFCs, ICs, Investment Funds Founded as Public Limited Company, OFIs (Fund Management Companies, Leasing Companies etc) and non-profit institutions serving households.

str:Concept.com:Name: Enterprise size
str:Concept.com:Description: Classification of enterprises by size, in accordance with the Annex to Commission Recommendation 2003/361/EC.

str:Concept.com:Name: Other entity code
str:Concept.com:Description: Other entity code

str:Concept.com:Name: Entity RIAD code
str:Concept.com:Description: The RIAD code is an alphanumeric code assigned to each entity recorded in RIAD. The RIAD code is exclusive, meaning that the same RIAD code cannot be allocated to more than one entity (even at different points in time), and is unique, meaning that a given entity has only one RIAD code. It is the responsibility of each NCB, for respective (resident) entities, to ensure that all entities with an official RIAD code represent distinct real world entities (unique identification).

str:Concept.com:Name: Entity role
str:Concept.com:Description: Role of the counterparties in an instrument.

str:Concept.com:Name: Código de Identificación Fiscal (NIF)
str:Concept.com:Description: Fiscal Identification Number

str:Concept.com:Name: Fiduciary instrument
str:Concept.com:Description: Identification of instruments in which the observed agent acts in its own name but on behalf of and with the risk borne by a third party.

str:Concept.com:Name: Arvonlisäverotunniste (ALV-tunnus)
str:Concept.com:Description: The VAT number indicates that a business is VAT liable is essential for the functioning and controlling of the intra-Community trade. VAT liable businesses that are engaged in intra-Community trade form their VAT number themselves.

str:Concept.com:Name: Rahastotunnus (SIRA-tunnus)
str:Concept.com:Description: Identifier to identify the investment fund in the authority reporting (NCB / NCA). Normally given by the NCA - in some cases by NCB.

str:Concept.com:Name: Off-balance sheet amount
str:Concept.com:Description: Total nominal amount of off-balance sheet exposures. This includes any commitment to lend before considering conversion factors and credit risk mitigation techniques. It is the amount that best represents the institution's maximum exposure to credit risk without taking into account any protection held or other credit enhancements.

str:Concept.com:Name: Original protection value
str:Concept.com:Description: The protection’s fair value at the date when it was originally received as a credit protection.

str:Concept.com:Name: Outstanding nominal amount
str:Concept.com:Description: Principal amount outstanding at the end of the reporting reference date, including unpaid past due interest but excluding accrued interest. The outstanding nominal amount must be reported net of write-offs and write-downs as determined by the relevant accounting practices.

str:Concept.com:Description: The maximum amount of the protection value that can be considered as credit protection for the instrument. The amount of the existing third parties or observed agent priority claims against the protection must be excluded in the protection allocated value. For protections that is eligible under Regulation (EU) No 575/2013, this value should be reported in accordance with Part 2 of Annex V to Implementing Regulation (EU) No 680/2014.

str:Concept.com:Name: Protection identifier
str:Concept.com:Description: An identifier applied by the reporting agent to uniquely identify each protection used to secure the instrument. Each protection must have one protection identifier. This value will not change over time and cannot be used as the protection identifier for any other protection.

str:Concept.com:Name: Protection value
str:Concept.com:Description: The amount of the protection value as established for the relevant ‘Type of protection value’ following the valuation approach.

str:Concept.com:Name: Protection valuation approach
str:Concept.com:Description: Type of protection valuation; method used to determine the protection value.

str:Concept.com:Name: Provisions associated with off-balance sheet exposures

The provision of an “Other” identifier is generally Page 13 of 163 seen as an option of last resort to be used in case none of the pre-defined identifiers are available for that entity.
